    <h2>What to Look for in a Commercial Bakery Oven</h2>
    <p><strong>Temperature uniformity:</strong> The most critical spec. An oven that bakes unevenly is a nightmare — you'll constantly rotate trays and deal with inconsistent results. Ask for temperature mapping data.</p>
    <p><strong>Temperature range:</strong> Most baking is done between 160°C and 240°C. Some products (like meringues) need lower temperatures; some (like pizza) need higher. Ensure the oven covers your required range.</p>
    <p><strong>Recovery time:</strong> After loading a cold batch, how quickly does the oven return to target temperature? Fast recovery means you can bake back-to-back without waiting.</p>
    <p><strong>Energy efficiency:</strong> Look for ovens with good insulation and energy efficiency ratings. In a bakery running 8–12 hours daily, energy costs are significant.</p>
    <p><strong>Programmability:</strong> Modern commercial ovens can store hundreds of baking programmes. Once you've perfected a recipe, you can reproduce it exactly every time — vital for consistency.</p>
    <p><strong>Build quality and durability:</strong> Commercial ovens should last 10–15+ years. Stainless steel construction, robust hinges, quality door seals, and reliable thermostats are all indicators of quality.</p>

    <div class="faq-section">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">Which commercial oven is best for a new bakery in India? <span class="icon">+</span></button>
        <div class="faq-a">For most new bakeries in India, a Sinmag 8-tray convection oven (₹1,20,000 – ₹1,60,000) is the best starting point. It offers good quality at a reasonable price, is widely used in India so service is available, and handles a wide range of products. If you're primarily baking bread, add a 2-deck Sinmag deck oven. Budget total: ₹2,00,000 – ₹3,50,000.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">Is Sinmag a good oven for Indian bakeries? <span class="icon">+</span></button>
        <div class="faq-a">Yes. Sinmag is probably the most popular mid-range bakery oven brand in India. Taiwanese-made, reliable, and backed by a reasonable service network. For the price, it offers excellent value. Many successful bakeries across India use Sinmag equipment. Read our detailed review: <a href="/blog/sinmag-oven-review">Sinmag Oven Review India</a>.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">What size convection oven do I need for my bakery? <span class="icon">+</span></button>
        <div class="faq-a">Estimate your daily production volume first. A standard commercial tray holds approximately 12 cookies, 6 small loaves, or 8 muffins. An 8-tray oven can bake 8 trays per cycle; cycles take 15–30 minutes. So in 8 hours, you can complete roughly 20–30 cycles — that's 160–240 trays of baking. If your production requirement exceeds this, you need a larger oven or multiple ovens.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">How much electricity does a commercial bakery oven use? <span class="icon">+</span></button>
        <div class="faq-a">An 8-tray electric convection oven typically uses 6–10 kWh per hour at full operation. Running 8 hours a day, that's 48–80 kWh per day, or approximately ₹384–₹640 per day at ₹8/kWh commercial rate. Gas-fired ovens typically cost 30–40% less to run than electric in India. A 2-deck gas oven running 8 hours might consume gas worth ₹150–₹250 per day.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">Can I buy a commercial oven on EMI in India? <span class="icon">+</span></button>
        <div class="faq-a">Yes. Most equipment suppliers in India offer EMI options through NBFCs or bank partnerships. You typically need to pay 20–30% down payment with the balance over 12–36 months. Interest rates range from 12–24% depending on your credit profile. For larger purchases (above ₹5L), MSME loans and government schemes may offer better rates. Read our full guide: <a href="/blog/bakery-equipment-financing">How to Finance Bakery Equipment in India</a>.</div>
